Device Comment: vessel:polarstern:gravimeter - A gravimeter is used to measure accelerations due to the gravitational field of the earth. The gravimeter on board of Polarstern is situated on a gyro-stabilized platform to compensate for the ship's movement. It is a spring and mass system with magnetic compensation, the extension of the spring being proportional to the gravitational force.

vessel:polarstern:pco2_go_ps - The Model 8050 pCO2 Measuring System is an autonomous analytical system for online measurement of the mixing ratio (partial pressure) of carbon dioxide in oceanic surface water and in the marine atmosphere.
vessel:polarstern:svt - SVP is meant to be installed in RV Polarstern box keel at depth of 11m. Measurement data are primarily used as c-keel values for echo sounder systems Parasound and Hydrosweep.

vessel:polarstern:tsk1 - The thermosalinograph is an instrument used to accurately determine sea surface conductivity and temperature. The remote temperature sensor SBE38 is integrated with the SBE21 Thermosalinograph.?

vessel:polarstern:tsk2 - The thermosalinograph is an instrument used to accurately determine sea surface conductivity and temperature. The remote temperature sensor SBE38 is integrated with the SBE21 Thermosalinograph.?
ferrybox:soop_pamos_001 - Portable atmospheric measurement box on sea (PAMOS) for deployment on ships to measure aerosols, trace gases, and meteorological parameters.
vessel:soop_fridtjof_nansen:soop_pamos_003 - Portable atmospheric measurement box on sea (PAMOS) for deployment on ships to measure aerosols, trace gases, and meteorological parameters.

vessel:polarstern:magnetometer - Magnetometers are used to measure the earth magnetic field. The magnetometer on board of Polarstern is a vector magnetometer that measures the vector components of the magnetic field. It consists of an upper and a lower sensor.

vessel:polarstern:weather - The weather station at Polarstern consists of several devices which measure standard parameters such as temperature, wind, humidity, barometric pressure, radiation and precipitation. Satellite images are received with a dedicated antenna which, together with the data, are used for forecast purposes. The station is operated by a weather technician-observer from the German Weather Service (DWD) who is responsible for the routine 3-hourly synoptic observations and the daily upper air soundings.?

vessel:polarstern:neutron_monitor - Neutron monitors are ground-based devices to measure the variation of cosmic ray intensities. The instrument is a counter?designed to detect nucleonic components of cascades initiated by primary cosmic particles in the atmosphere.

vessel:polarstern:myon_detector - The device detects cosmic particles (mainly myons) which are produced by the reaction of cosmic radiation with atomic nuclei or molecules in the upper atmosphere. The system consists of 2 sensor boxes, a data aquisiton system, GPS antenna and a netbook.

vessel:polarstern:adcp - The Acoustic Doppler Current Profiler (ADCP) measures flow rates in the water body below the moving vessel with an operating frequency of 150 kHz. Up to 400m range can be achieved according to the data sheet.
vessel:polarstern:fb_ps - The FerryBox is an automatic, flow-through system to measure water parameters (e.g. temperature, conductivity, sound velocity, pH, fluorescence) continously and unattended.
vessel:polarstern:simrad_ek_60___ek_80 - The sounder operates several frequencies simultaneously thus allowing to detect fish in different depths.

vessel:polarstern:gravimeter - A gravimeter is used to measure accelerations due to the gravitational field of the earth. The gravimeter on board of Polarstern is situated on a gyro-stabilized platform to compensate for the ship's movement. It is a spring and mass system with magnetic compensation, the extension of the spring being proportional to the gravitational force.

vessel:polarstern:pco2_go_ps - The Model 8050 pCO2 Measuring System is an autonomous analytical system for online measurement of the mixing ratio (partial pressure) of carbon dioxide in oceanic surface water and in the marine atmosphere.
vessel:polarstern:svt - SVP is meant to be installed in RV Polarstern box keel at depth of 11m. Measurement data are primarily used as c-keel values for echo sounder systems Parasound and Hydrosweep.

vessel:polarstern:tsk1 - The thermosalinograph is an instrument used to accurately determine sea surface conductivity and temperature. The remote temperature sensor SBE38 is integrated with the SBE21 Thermosalinograph.?

vessel:polarstern:tsk2 - The thermosalinograph is an instrument used to accurately determine sea surface conductivity and temperature. The remote temperature sensor SBE38 is integrated with the SBE21 Thermosalinograph.?
vessel:polarstern:simrad_ek_60___ek_80 - The sounder operates several frequencies simultaneously thus allowing to detect fish in different depths.
vessel:polarstern:fb_ps - The FerryBox is an automatic, flow-through system to measure water parameters (e.g. temperature, conductivity, sound velocity, pH, fluorescence) continously and unattended.

vessel:polarstern:magnetometer - Magnetometers are used to measure the earth magnetic field. The magnetometer on board of Polarstern is a vector magnetometer that measures the vector components of the magnetic field. It consists of an upper and a lower sensor.
